2.5. SEPARABILITY 11
Denition 2.4.1: Algebraic Closure
Given a eld F , a eld F is the algebraic closure of F if
(a). F is algebraic over F ,
(b). Every polynomial f (x) F [x] splits completely over F
Recall that splitting completely implies that f (x) factors into a product of degree 1 polynomials.
Denition 2.4.2: Algebraically Closed
A eld K is algebraically closed if every polynomial with coecients in K has a root in K.
Proposition 2.4.1
If F is the algebraic closure of F , then F is algebraically closed.
